The paper discusses approaches to content-and-structure XML retrieval, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) that deals with structured data. The paper also discusses the use of eXist, a native XML database (cs.DB), and proposes a novel retrieval model that utilizes structural relationships between answer elements, which is relevant to deep learning (cs.DL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the retrieval of specific elements within articles, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
